isOverlappingAllowed

public boolean isOverlappingAllowed()
Description copied from class: MapObject
Determine whether overlapping with this object in general is allowed. This is sort of a physicsy thing. Allowing it implies no physical presence on the map, even if this object has a hitbox. Disallowing it is usually a signal that collisions need to be resolvled.

Specified by:
isOverlappingAllowed in class MapObject
Returns:
True if overlapping with this object is okay
See Also:
MapObject.isOverlappingAllowed()
